Gemini said
*Smart COD: Secure, Automated, and Ready!*




Managing Cash on Delivery (COD) comes with operational risk =E2=80=94 from
assigning the right riders to controlling how much cash is held in the
field.
With this release, we=E2=80=99re introducing a *comprehensive COD managemen=
t
system* that
gives you full control over *who handles cash, how much they carry, and
what happens when limits are breached* =E2=80=94 now with *more flexibility=
 in
order allocation control*.
What=E2=80=99s New




Controlled COD Allocation (Eligibility-Based)

Define which riders are eligible to handle COD orders using criteria like:

   -

   Lifetime completed orders
   -

   Orders in the last 7 days
   -

   Average daily performance

  Riders who don=E2=80=99t qualify: Will *not receive COD orders *and will =
*continue
receiving prepaid orders.*


Cash Limits with Configurable Enforcement


Set limits on how much cash a rider can hold:

   -

   Max cash outstanding - Maximum cash a rider can hold at any time
   (including cash in hand + cash from newly allocated orders)
   -

   Excess over daily earnings (enabled with Earnings & Incentives module)
   -

   Excess over weekly earnings (enabled with Earnings & Incentives module)


*NOTE: The limits apply considering new orders will also be allocated. So a
single order or all orders in a route will be checked to ensure the limits
are met.*


Rider breaching the defined limits


You now have *flexibility in how strictly you want to enforce restrictions*=
:

   -

   *Block All Order Allocation* (COD + Prepaid)
   -

   *Block Only COD Order Allocation*
   -

   *Take No Action initially and monitor your patterns to enforce cleaner
   restrictions later*

This allows you to balance *risk control with operational continuity*.


Smart Alerts & Threshold Monitoring


Introducing the new *=E2=80=9CCash Exceeded Threshold=E2=80=9D alert*:

   -

   Auto-triggers when limits are breached
   -

   Linked directly to configured cash thresholds
   -

   Supports automated actions for faster resolution
   -

      *Logout Rider from Shift*
      -

      *Assign Admin Task to return to hub and deposit cash*


What This Means To YouGemini said



   -

   Assign COD orders only to *qualified riders*
   -

   Control how much cash is in the field at any time
   -

   Choose between *strict blocking or partial restriction* based on your
   operations
   -

   Take no immediate action for rider operations but get notified in
   realtime to observe rider behaviour
   -

   Automate enforcement and reduce manual monitoring
   -

   Improve cash reconciliation and reduce leakage risk


What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
